caption: Went here to have dinner just for myself. I was so looking forward to prime rib night. Many tables out front. Hostess told me that they are short staffed so I had to go on wait list. Mind you I saw like seven tables on porch open.  I said okay how long? Her response was I don’t know because a lot of people will stay here all night to listen to music and drink. I said thanks and I’ll eat somewhere else. It’s a shame to because I literally ate here with my entire family of 10 three months ago. I don’t know if I’ll ever go back again.

My mother and I stopped by for an impromptu lunch today.   I had been wanting to try this place based on the recommendation of a friend.  Upon arriving, I immediately had a bad feeling about this place.  We had to seat ourselves on the veranda and waited over fifteen minutes for a server to show up.  The waitress that did show up was very friendly and attentive throughout our meal however her sweet personality could not make up for the poor quality of the food.  We ordered two appetizers consisting of the Konch Fritters and the Boom Boom Shrimp.   The fritters had been over fried and were almost burnt.  The shrimp didn't appear to be fully cooked and the garnish it was served with was wilted and most likely several days old.  We followed up with the Fried Grouper Sandwich and a Cuban, both served with coleslaw.  The Grouper sandwich was tasty but the Cuban was fatty and had too much mustard on it that you couldn't taste the meat.  The ciabatta role was very dry and most likely stale.  The worst part of our meal was the coleslaw, which lacked any kind of dressing.  It was simply shredded cabbage with some carrot, which most likely came out of a bag.  We had soft drinks with our meal and passed on the  desserts not wanting to be further disappointed.  Our bill with tip came to nearly $70.  There are many other restaurants in the immediate area where you can get a very fresh and tasty meal for that kind of money.  I suppose many of the patrons of this place primarily go there for the alcohol and entertainment.  I cannot in good conscience recommend Duval Street for it's food.  I will not be returning.

2nd time I went there for prime rib night. Starts at 4pm . Only waited 10 min for a table but they were  sold out of prime rib by 630.  I don’t understand how that could happen. It don’t go bad ,if you use it for roast beef sandwiches if you have extra.  My opinion. Poor management.   I’m a restaurant owner

I do understand that this establishment opened under new owners in the last three months, but this does not explain why we were treated by some in our visit to eat. A group of friends stopped at the outside bar there a week or so ago around lunchtime, the bartender (Jeff I think was his name..) was a very friendly, engaging person so we choose to stop in later that week for dinner. This is where it went straight downhill, 6 of us waited for an outdoor table with plenty of them vacant as we walked in. The hostess was working very hard, running all over the place after we let her know how many in our group... she seemed the only one who was concerned about work, the remainder of the staff not so much. A person who I believe was the owner came out, sat at the reservation podium and after an uncomfortable amount of time, looked up at us and asked if we were being taken care of, he immediately looked down, flipped through the reservation book and said the hostess will take care of us. After an uncomfortable amount of tine (NOT the hostess's fault!) we were seated. Our server came over with drink and food menu's and took our drink order, it took at least 10 minutes to receive our drinks , so we did not let her get away and placed our food order. The second round of drinks again took a long, long time with no real excuse whey... the establishment was slowing down due to the later hour we were there, folks ate and left. Our server was not at fault, clearly the owner needs to be much more involved and caring about his business if in fact he was the owner (as he told a member of our group he was), we as a group discussed how very long it took to be seated and very long to receive our first and second drinks, the bartender is clearly not good at that job being it was relatively slow during our visit (Jeff the bartender was not working that evening!) One of our food orders was under cooked, and a wine was served that had soured.. again our server was very caring and attentive, not so much the other staff. We love the way the establishment looked outside and in, but unless the owner and bartender(s) and the cook steps up their game, you may not want to stop in for a meal, if the owner does not care, why should some of the staff?

If I could leave zero stars I would!!! This place is absolutely horrible!!! From the parking, to the service, to the food. We were there an hour and 12 minutes and our dinner showed up, but not our appetizer. We had to ask twice for refills on the drinks. The excuse was "I have to wait on the bar." There was nobody at the bar. We were not the only table to complain either. There were two other tables we saw that complained. There was also one table that got up and left. The waitresses and the bus girl were also extremely rude when walking through tables and making the customers move in their chairs so they could get by, instead of walking around and not interrupting the customers. We were also double charged for something on the bill, which was eventually fixed after a lengthy period. Our waitress never even asked us how our meal was during or after. There were 11 waitresses I counted, and only ten tables occupied in the dining room. It should not have take over an hour to cook a chicken breast, two burgers, and a crab cake appetizer. On top of that the two hostesses were very sloppily dressed. One was wearing a hoodie, and one was in a jacket that did not even let anyone know they were members of the staff. The whole staff was totally unprofessional, and unorganized. We will not be returning to this restaurant ever again. Do not let the pictures fool you that have been posted. They don't have any of that on the menu!!!

Mother's day weekend specials tonight were amazing. Plus the added lil necks. Endless mimosas and desert 45 per person. It's well worth it. Met the owner chief and staff. Great time. There is passion in food in the cape.

Very clean establishment, unique team with outstanding service and the best ribeye with shrimp parmesan topping. Everything was seasoned perfectly and the passion from the kitchen was deliciously tasted with every bite. Local and returning
I've eaten here several time. Beautiful gourmet food at a very reasonable price

My sister and myself stopped in yesterday and we were very surprised. Immediately were welcomed by the staff and instantly had that key west feel. The music was islandy, the kitchen is open and unique and how very clean. Our dinners were Duval Crawl (lobster) with delicious broccolini. We both chose soup instead of salad(Butternut squash with pepitas) amazing. Just all around a very pleasant experience. We absolutely recommend and will be back.
Great.  Delicious Bread with Almond Butter, Coconut Shrimp,Twice Baked Potato and Zucchini Squash
Extra nice new and getting better with a future outdoor bar coming real nice people and owners

Absolutely amazing food, atmosphere and customer service.  I gave a 5 star to everything I ate.  I even tasted the other 4 people that I dined with and everything was so delicious.  They have the BEST almond butter EVER.  I will definitely go back.

Great menu. Something for everyone. Fresh seafood, steaks, pasta.   Stone crab chowder was fabulous.  Fresh snapper was beautifully prepared and properly cooked. Baby back ribs were also very good. Sauce wasn't too sweet which is my normal complaint.  Key lime pie is authentic. Excellent Caesar salad as well.  They have inly been open for a few weeks, but food and service were great.

This was the 2nd time I've eaten that Duval's as they've recently opened the food is absolutely wonderful and the menu choice is plentiful highly recommend you give this new Cape Coral restaurant a try I think it will become a gem

There are still kinks to work out.  The pasta dishes were very good, the steaks also, but one meal came out wrong and the $32 scallops couldn't be found on the plate.  The waitress was great and handled everything beautifully.  The kitchen will be the downfall if they dont get their act together.  The place should have been busting at the seams with diners but it wasn't.   I hope they are still there when I want to return.

Laid back but elegant!  If you don't have the urge to line dance and you left your cowboy boots and hat at home, stop in here!  No loud music but Key West inspired theme of nearly fine dining worth experiencing more than once. Why? You just can't decide which menu item this time so you must return to try them all!  Service was spot on without being too overbearing.
Good atmosphere and very good service and food. Plate presentation is beautiful.
The food is excellent. Restaurant is comfortable. They are kid friendly.

Last night my husband and our two friends went to Duval’s. First of all the ambience was wonderful really friendly feel as you walk in and the decor is gorgeous! We all had drinks and our waitress was very friendly. The food was outstanding my husband had the Ribeye,  I had the 6oz filet, our friends had the ribeye and Ribs! Wish I had taken pictures everything absolutely cooked to perfection, now for dessert we had the pineapple rum cake omg delicious and our friends had a chocolate mousse which was delicious too. I would highly recommend Duval’s. Something definitely needed in the Cape.

(Translated by Google) Really good restaurant: very good food, friendly staff and nice atmosphere. We recommend it. Caesar  (Original) Vraiment un bon restaurant:  nourriture très bonne, personnel sympathique et belle ambiance. On le recommande. César

My husband and I had a very pleasant dinner at Duval's last night. We started with a bottle of house pinot noir that was good and very reasonably priced. We shared the ahi tuna bites and it was fresh, well presented and good sized. We both got crisp cesar salads with our dinners. My husband got prime rib, medium rare. It was well cooked and seasoned nicely. I got a Florida lobster tail. It was very good as well. For dessert, we shared a rum soaked pineapple upside down cake. It was warm and fresh! The service was very good but not intrusive. The only negative for us was that we felt that a restaurant of this caliber and price should not have vinyl table cloths and paper napkins. Overall, our experience was wonderful!
Great food, great service!

My wife is pregnant and was looking for some great food in the Cape. She didn't want good food rather great food. After looking at half a dozen menus online Duval's was the clear winner.  We had friends over and she was not feeling like going out but was desperate for what we saw so a buddy of mine and I headed down to grab it as take out and left the ladies at home.  Duvals is new and was not set up for take out in their first week but the staff went out of their way to find a way to pack up 4 meals so that we could take them home.  The food: The homemade bread and sweet almond butter is reason enough to go alone. Thats right almond butter. I'm not an alternative butter kind of guy but this stuff is like magic frosting on pillow soft bread we watched come right out of the oven.  The homemade coconut shrimp, stuffed mushrooms and conch fritters were all worthy of their own Jimmy Buffett chorus. When it came time for the Entre we did the thing you aren't supposed to do at a place with great seafood and ordered the prime rib. I do not regret this choice one bit. The PR was amazing! Cooked perfectly with great spice, flavor and an au jus that with change you. Cap off the night with their version of key lime pie which is more like a key lime tart in its graham cracker to filling recipe but outside monroe county FL its one of the best I've had.  I mentioned the staff: In many restaurants getting your order right, quick and with a smile gets 5 star service. At Duval's there was personality, fun, and a genuine feeling that they cared about the food they were serving and the people they were serving it to.  With the right ingredients you can have 5 star food, but it takes the right staff to have a 5 star restaurant.  Congratulations on being our new favorite spot in the Cape

We are thrilled with the new restaurant, Duval’s, in Cape Coral. As fans of Key West, we love the ambience and special items on the menu. We had conch fritters for our appetizer and then I enjoyed the red snapper with crab meat topping. My husband had shrimp and grits. Accompanying each entree were a salad and vegetable and starch. I had double vegetables (a heavenly squash medley).  Well, folks, our food was divine. We have eaten in some very excellent restaurants like Roy’s and Ruth’s Chris Steakhouse and Duval’s is right up there with the best. Our server, Daniela, was absolutely spectacular. What a sweetheart! She was kind but not intrusive. We really liked her.  I realize that I am using a lot of exaggerated language for Duval’s, but this restaurant deserves every single word.
Everything about this restaurant are a refreshing change for Cape Coral the food was exceptionally and the coconut shrimp was fantastic

Wonderful atmosphere, attentive service, reasonable prices and great food. My husband had a chicken dish with broccolini and twice baked potato which was delicious. I had shrimp and grits...and this is the reason for four stars. The shrimp were fantastic, but the grits were bland and doughy...definitely could stand improvement!! Their fresh bread with almond butter is awesome. Excellent service. A great addition to the Cape restaurant scene!! Highly recommend!!
Great meals, polite and attentive staff, nice atmosphere.  We will be back again.

Great addition to the cape. I had the Conch fritters and they were very good.  I'll definitely come back to try an entre with my husband.  Try a specialty drink, I usually drink wine but is was nice to change it up. Staff was very attentive, unlike some of the restaurants in the area.

Great addition to the choices for fine dining in Cape Coral.  Duval’s is located on the newly redone 47th Terrace right at the Vincennes rotary.  The interior is refreshingly pleasant and the staff is very accommodating.  We dined there looking for a variety.  Our main courses were baby back ribs and snapper.  Both were very tasty with wonderful presentation.  Our server, Melissa, was extremely professional.  She was there for us when needed without being obtrusive.  Prices were very much inline with the quality of the food.  We look forward to returning to this establishment.
